laboratory_examinations.findings: Left ventricular ejection fraction (LVEF) of 25% with anteroseptal, anterior, and apical akinesis.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Stable ejection fraction of 25% since post-MI echocardiogram.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Normal sinus rhythm with normal intervals and QRS axis. Anterior Q waves with T-wave inversions, consistent with large anterior MI.
